NEW BOOK ALERT

“Everything I’m Trying to Tell You”
Published by @superlabo 

Link to preorder in bio ✨

Initially conceived as a twenty-year color retrospective, “Everything I’m Trying to Tell You” materialized into a much more private body of work, largely shaped by a summer of complicated personal experiences.

“I found myself on these road trips, alone, out in the middle of nowhere. I just had my camera. I was wandering, drawn to the most strange and remote places. It was a period when my relationship with photography changed, it became a tool to process what was happening in my life. Once editing, I found myself drawn to different material. The old pictures had different meaning. After some time I realized that what I wanted to say with this book went beyond words. It was about the feelings that I couldn’t express or understand. This was its purpose.”

– Greg Hunt

Available for preorder
Releasing April 28
Customers who preorder by April 27 receive a signed “photo card”

My old friend @samesk8r recently found this footage of us skating Ann Arbor, Michigan back in 1989. I can’t explain how surreal it is for me to see this, it was so was rare for there to be a camera on the streets back then, I don’t remember any of it. We were 15! Featured mostly is @dj50one50 one of my best friends at the time and who first introduced me to skateboarding. Also appearing are @this_dog_is_crazy @samesk8r and Dave Roberts. Graffiti at the end is by A2 legend @yerboy 🫡
Skateboarding was our entire world back then. Ann Arbor was an epic scene at the time. We were very lucky. 
PS I’m pretty sure we knew those girls at the Taco Bell and were just having some fun 😎
Thank you Rob for digging this up!
🙏
